# Trivy escapes for the e2e-smoke image scan (ci.yml points here, so the file
# must exist even when empty — tests/test_ci_artifacts.py asserts that).
#
# Any entry must carry a justification + an explicit removal condition,
# and (when the advisory also appears in the PyPI feed) be mirrored as a
# pip-audit --ignore-vuln escape in ci.yml plus an entry in the
# TestVulnEscapesCannotRot.ESCAPED map so it cannot rot.
# (Python-side escapes are currently ZERO — WP-14 bumped langchain-core
# to 1.4.4, clearing CVE-2026-34070 and CVE-2026-44843.)
#
# CVE-2026-42504 — Go stdlib (net/mail MIME decoding) v1.26.3 compiled INTO
# the upstream caddy binary in caddy:2-alpine. Not fixable on our side (apk
# cannot patch a static Go binary); Caddy does not parse inbound MIME mail.
# REMOVE when caddy:2-alpine ships a binary built with Go >= 1.26.4
# (docker pull && trivy image caddy:2-alpine to check).
CVE-2026-42504
